    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-11-27T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-11-27T20:00:00-05:00" n="758"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d758">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.003 C 73/351: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-11-27T20:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 27, 1926—8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>285. Department is publishing report of Extraterritorial[ity] Commission on
                    November 29.<note n="69" xml:id="d758fn69">Department of State, <hi
                            rend="italic">Report of the Commission on Extraterritoriality in China,
                            Peking, September 16, 1926</hi> (Washington, Government Printing Office,
                        1926).</note> This date has been notified to other <pb facs="1116" n="984"
                        xml:id="pg_984"/> governments concerned and it is understood that
                    publication will be made in other capitals on same date except in London where
                    there has been delay due to lateness of receiving report and getting it
                    printed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
